    {
      "id": "1450585697500004363",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-12-16T14:29:40.863-06:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "From a TPM lens, brand building usually shows up through execution. Things like running flawless large-scale launches with no customer impact, setting up clear customer-facing release readiness and comms, making partner integrations smooth and predictable, and leading strong incident response with transparent postmortems all build external trust. Over time, customers and partners associate the brand with reliability, scale, and operational maturity.",
      "author": {
        "id": "1369114689115783268",
        "name": "sree08202",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Sri D",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/0.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
      "mentions": [],
      "inlineEmojis": []
    },
    {
      "id": "1450630528519635198",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-12-16T17:27:49.411-06:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I think on scenario is how incidents are handled. Coordination, clear leadership communication, and postmortems with followup to close all open AI go a long way in building trust externally. Those wins and effort often stick more than success announcements.",
      "author": {
        "id": "921916180309086250",
        "name": "illusionustpanda",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "illusionustpanda",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/4.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
